Q: What are IAM?
User accounts managed by one administrator.
You can 
* create groups
* create users accounts
* setup a password policy
* create roles

!!! IAM is not to be confused with AMI, or Amazon Machine Image 

Q: Where is the IAM console?
https://console.aws.amazon.com/iam/home?#

Q: Where can I log if I have an IAM ?
https://770194671265.signin.aws.amazon.com/console
Note that 770194671265 is the administrative account (AWS Account ID).
!!! The user account is the one defined in the IAM console (emmanuel_mayssat)
!!! The User should also have a password that was assigned to him by the administrator
!!! > IAM > User > username > Security Credentials > (sign in credential) Manage Password

!!! NOTE THIS WEBSITE IS TO ACCESS THE SAME AMAZON ADMINISTRATIVE INTERFACE !!!

Q: What are users?
Users interact with websites and services.

Q: What are groups?
Groups enable you to manage permissions for multiple users.

Q: What Are Permissions?
Permissions specify which actions a user can perform.

Q: What Are Roles?
Roles allow AWS services and IAM users to act on your behalf.

Q: Amazon Resource Name?
arn:aws:s3:::example_bucket/developers/design_info.doc

#---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
# CREDENTIALS

Q: Access credentials vs sing-in credentials?
Sign-in credentials are used to log on the AWS website.
Access credentials is used by 3rd party applications to work as the user.

Q: How many access credentials can a user account have?
Many!
Each can be made active or inactive, or simply deleted.

#---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
# GROUP POLICY

Q: Group policy to access everything in S3?
{
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": "s3:*",
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}

Q: Group policy to everything in S3 with read only mode?
{
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:Get*",
        "s3:List*"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}

Q: Allow everything on a specific bucket?
{
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "Stmt1361595623860",
      "Action": [
        "s3:*"
      ],
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::mucls.lynceantech.com"
      ]
    }
  ]
}

Q: Group ARN ?
arn:aws:s3:

#---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
# POLICIES

